long_desc.thetext:
If there are more then one method with Java 8 labda expression in one class then content assist works only for lambda in the last method.

Example code:

import java.util.Optional;

public class LambdaBug {

	private final String field = "final field";

	void method1() {
		Optional.of("test").map(s -> {
			String local;
			// content assist doesn't work here
			return s;
		}).get();
	}

	void method2() {
		Optional.of("test").map(s -> {
			String local;
			// content assist works there
			return s;
		}).get();
	}

}


In this code snippet in first lambda expression content assist doesn't work at all. Even just defined local variable doesn't shown. But in the second method content assist works fine though the method code is 100% the same.
